# Implementation Plan: DirNav UI Component

- **Feature Branch**: main
- **Created**: 2026-05-13
- **Spec**: [spec.md](./spec.md)
- **Status**: Implemented

---

## Summary

DirNav is an OS-like floating window directory navigator built as a SolidJS + TypeScript component, distributable as an npm package. It embeds via shadow DOM for style isolation, supports four node types, and provides both mouse and full-keyboard control. Derived from FR-001 through FR-011 in [spec.md](./spec.md).

---

## Technical Context

| Dimension | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| Language | TypeScript |
| Framework | SolidJS (reactive signals, no virtual DOM) |
| Build | Vite |
| Testing | Playwright (component + e2e) |
| Storage | `localStorage` (window position, theme, input values) |
| Distribution | npm package (`github:mhixon/DirNav`) |
| Target platform | Browser (userscripts, web apps) |
| Style isolation | Shadow DOM ‚Äî mandatory, no external CSS dependencies |
| Performance goals | Search debounced; fuzzy results memoized; lazy virtual-dir loading |
| Constraints | Max 23 items per directory enforced at init; ES2020+ browsers only |

---

## Constitution Check

Pre-implementation gates (verify before story work begins):

- [x] No style leakage between component and host page (shadow DOM enforced).
- [x] localStorage failures are caught and fall back to defaults.
- [x] All keyboard shortcuts are cleaned up on unmount.
- [x] Virtual directory async operations are cancelled/ignored on unmount.
- [x] Tree validation runs before any render, throwing on violations.

---

## Architecture

### Component Hierarchy

```
DirnavUI (root ‚Äî manages all state, keyboard listeners)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Window (draggable/resizable shell)
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ TitleBar (back ‚Üê / command-palette > | directory name | ‚ñ° X)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ NavigationView (breadcrumbs + paginated item list)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ CommandPalette (fuzzy search input + result list)
```

### State Model

| State slice | Managed by | Persisted |
|-------------|-----------|-----------|
| `NavigationState` (path, directory, page, totalPages) | `DirnavUI` | No |
| `WindowState` (x, y, width, height, visible, focused) | `DirnavUI` | Yes ‚Äî position + size |
| `CommandPaletteState` (active, searchTerm, results, selectedIndex) | `DirnavUI` | No |
| Theme (light / dark / system) | `DirnavUI` | Yes |
| Input values (per-key) | `DirnavUI` | Yes |

### Data Flow

1. **Init** ‚Äî caller passes `DirectoryNode` tree; validator runs; shadow DOM attaches to `document.body`.
2. **Navigation** ‚Äî user interaction triggers signal updates ‚Üí `NavigationView` reacts ‚Üí breadcrumbs + item list re-render.
3. **Keyboard** ‚Äî global `keydown` listener on `document` handles all shortcuts; removed on cleanup.
4. **Persistence** ‚Äî `createEffect` writes window state + theme + input values to `localStorage` on change; read once on mount.
5. **Command Palette** ‚Äî activated by `>` button or `` ` `` key; fuzzy search runs over all leaf nodes on each keystroke (debounced).

### Keyboard Shortcut Map

| Key | Context | Action |
|-----|---------|--------|
| Ctrl+` | Global | Toggle show/hide/focus |
| 1‚Äì9 | Focused | Select item or change page |
| Backspace | Focused | Navigate up |
| Esc | Focused | Hide window (or clear search) |
| `` ` `` | Focused at root | Open command palette |
| Arrow Up/Down | Command palette | Move selection |
| Enter | Command palette | Activate selected item |

### Node Type Dispatch

| `type` | On select |
|--------|-----------|
| `directory` | Push to path, load children |
| `action` | Call `callback()` |
| `input` | Focus inline input; Enter ‚Üí save to localStorage; Esc ‚Üí cancel |
| `virtual` | Call async `action()`, show loader, render returned `DirectoryNode` |

### Pagination Strategy

- Max 9 items/page ‚Üí aligns with 1‚Äì9 keyboard shortcuts.
- Max 3 pages (23 items total) ‚Äî enforced at init.
- Item 1 = previous page (pages 2, 3); Item 9 = next page (pages 1, 2).
- Pagination dots indicate current page.

### Fuzzy Search

- Searches all leaf nodes (action, input, virtual) across entire tree.
- Relevance scored by match position and character coverage.
- Results sorted descending by score.
- Search input debounced to avoid excessive filtering on rapid typing.

